♪A sweet kiss and smile♪

52
00:04:39,600 --> 00:04:42,820
♪The moon shines through the light veil
as we cuddle♪

53
00:04:44,000 --> 00:04:46,880
♪You've never seen a jade so beautiful♪

54
00:04:46,980 --> 00:04:49,060
(Qipei Pavilion)
Mr. Hao, please let me go.

55
00:04:49,060 --> 00:04:50,300
I have a family

56
00:04:50,300 --> 00:04:51,220
to feed.

57
00:04:51,220 --> 00:04:52,420
Go, go, go.

58
00:04:52,420 --> 00:04:54,380
Don't think I don't know
where you're going.

59
00:04:55,980 --> 00:04:58,420
Madam took you in
when you were at your lowest.

60
00:04:58,860 --> 00:05:00,100
Now that there's trouble,

61
00:05:00,100 --> 00:05:01,500
you're running to the Su family.

62
00:05:01,780 --> 00:05:03,780
How can you be so ungrateful?

63
00:05:03,780 --> 00:05:05,340
I have no other choice.

64
00:05:05,340 --> 00:05:06,220
Let him go.

65
00:05:08,220 --> 00:05:09,180
Young Master.

66
00:05:09,180 --> 00:05:11,660
(Bright and Perfect)

67
00:05:11,660 --> 00:05:13,620
Young Master, I am deeply sorry.

68
00:05:14,860 --> 00:05:15,780
No need to say more.

69
00:05:16,620 --> 00:05:17,580
It's hard for everyone.

70
00:05:17,780 --> 00:05:18,620
Shopkeeper Hao,

71
00:05:18,980 --> 00:05:21,420
settle his account and let him go.

72
00:05:27,100 --> 00:05:28,140
Go, go, go.

73
00:05:28,620 --> 00:05:29,820
Sorry, Young Master.

74
00:05:38,500 --> 00:05:40,020
Mother, why are you here?

75
00:05:41,180 --> 00:05:43,700
This is my dowry from my wedding.

76
00:05:43,940 --> 00:05:45,100
Use it for emergencies.

77
00:05:46,500 --> 00:05:48,740
No, I can't accept this, Madam.

78
00:05:48,740 --> 00:05:50,140
Why not?

79
00:05:50,500 --> 00:05:51,940
It's useless sitting here.

80
00:05:51,940 --> 00:05:53,260
Every little bit helps.

81
00:05:53,700 --> 00:05:55,820
These things are your memories.

82
00:05:55,820 --> 00:05:57,420
You can't lose them.

83
00:05:57,420 --> 00:05:59,180
What's more important

84
00:05:59,180 --> 00:06:01,580
than the people closest to me?

85
00:06:01,940 --> 00:06:03,380
These are just things.

86
00:06:03,820 --> 00:06:06,220
Surviving this crisis is what matters.

87
00:06:07,180 --> 00:06:08,020
No, you can't do this.

88
00:06:11,500 --> 00:06:12,340
Madam,

89
00:06:12,620 --> 00:06:14,340
I don't believe you don't care.

90
00:06:15,060 --> 00:06:17,500
These things must be important to you.

91
00:06:17,940 --> 00:06:20,340
How about this? You keep them.

92
00:06:20,860 --> 00:06:22,380
We'll think of a way together.

93
00:06:22,380 --> 00:06:23,620
We can get through this.

94
00:06:36,620 --> 00:06:37,540
Madam,

95
00:06:38,420 --> 00:06:39,740
these might be

96
00:06:39,740 --> 00:06:43,020
my dowry one day.

97
00:06:43,500 --> 00:06:44,340
Please.

98
00:06:45,180 --> 00:06:46,780
It wouldn't be right to sell them.

99
00:06:59,140 --> 00:07:01,180
Alright. We'll keep them.

100
00:07:02,060 --> 00:07:02,900
I won't sell them.

101
00:07:04,620 --> 00:07:05,460
I won't sell them.

102
00:07:07,300 --> 00:07:09,860
What did you tell my mother?

103
00:07:09,860 --> 00:07:10,820
- Secret.
- Secret.

104
00:07:12,940 --> 00:07:13,780
Well...

105
00:07:25,820 --> 00:07:26,700
I have an idea.

106
00:07:32,420 --> 00:07:34,140
What? Not making jade anymore?

107
00:07:34,820 --> 00:07:36,500
How can we make jade without jade?

108
00:07:36,740 --> 00:07:37,700
That's not right.

109
00:07:38,020 --> 00:07:40,020
The Qipei Pavilion has been proud
of this for generations.

110
00:07:40,020 --> 00:07:41,180
We can't just give up.

111
00:07:41,180 --> 00:07:42,020
Yes.

112
00:07:42,020 --> 00:07:44,540
We've made jade for generations
because we had jade.

113
00:07:44,740 --> 00:07:45,940
But without jade,

114
00:07:45,940 --> 00:07:47,940
should we starve everyone?

115
00:07:48,260 --> 00:07:49,100
But

116
00:07:49,940 --> 00:07:52,940
isn't this giving in to Su Jue?

117
00:07:52,940 --> 00:07:54,060
No.

118
00:07:54,060 --> 00:07:56,060
It's not forever.

119
00:07:56,060 --> 00:07:57,980
This is a temporary strategy.

120
00:07:58,180 --> 00:08:00,940
It's a tactical retreat.

121
00:08:01,940 --> 00:08:04,500
Mr. Pei, Dandan is right.

122
00:08:04,820 --> 00:08:06,820
If there's no better solution,

123
00:08:06,820 --> 00:08:07,940
let's find a way

124
00:08:07,940 --> 00:08:10,340
to keep Qipei Pavilion afloat for now.

125
00:08:10,940 --> 00:08:11,780
Right, Young Master.

126
00:08:12,140 --> 00:08:13,900
I think Ms. Shuangshuang is right.

127
00:08:14,180 --> 00:08:16,380
"A wise man does not fight
when the odds are against him."

128
00:08:16,380 --> 00:08:17,300
When we prosper,

129
00:08:17,300 --> 00:08:19,060
we'll buy out Suyu Pavilion.

130
00:08:19,940 --> 00:08:21,140
So you mean

131
00:08:21,940 --> 00:08:24,140
we'll make gold and silver jewelry?

132
00:08:26,380 --> 00:08:28,700
Not just gold and silver.

133
00:08:28,700 --> 00:08:30,580
Stone, wood,

134
00:08:30,580 --> 00:08:32,460
fabric, and even shells.

135
00:08:32,740 --> 00:08:34,660
As long as it's not jade, we'll make it.

136
00:08:34,900 --> 00:08:37,140
Su Jue likes making jade, right?

137
00:08:37,140 --> 00:08:38,500
Let him do it.

138
00:08:38,740 --> 00:08:39,740
It sounds like

139
00:08:39,740 --> 00:08:40,900
Qipei Pavilion's products

140
00:08:40,900 --> 00:08:41,940
will diversify.

141
00:08:44,020 --> 00:08:46,860
And you've seen
the previous low-cost jewelry

142
00:08:46,860 --> 00:08:47,900
and scented jade.

143
00:08:47,900 --> 00:08:49,500
The market response was great.

144
00:08:49,740 --> 00:08:50,660
New things

145
00:08:50,660 --> 00:08:53,140
are always popular.

146
00:08:53,460 --> 00:08:55,860
If we specialize in jewelry,

147
00:08:56,260 --> 00:08:58,540
the business won't be worse than before.

148
00:08:59,620 --> 00:09:01,460
Mr. Pei, you're skilled in jade carving,

149
00:09:01,780 --> 00:09:04,340
so gold and silver
should be easy for you.

150
00:09:05,020 --> 00:09:06,020
I know a bit.

151
00:09:06,020 --> 00:09:06,860
That's great.

152
00:09:07,100 --> 00:09:08,100
With my sister's designs

153
00:09:08,100 --> 00:09:09,940
and Mr. Pei's help,

154
00:09:10,460 --> 00:09:11,700
we'll produce masterpieces.

155
00:09:12,460 --> 00:09:13,620
As for the craftsmen,

156
00:09:13,620 --> 00:09:15,860
they're almost familiar with it,

157
00:09:16,100 --> 00:09:17,660
so they'll adapt quickly.

158
00:09:17,980 --> 00:09:19,860
As for the shopkeepers and clerks,

159
00:09:19,860 --> 00:09:21,100
they'll manage smoothly.

160
00:09:21,620 --> 00:09:23,380
Everything is ready.

161
00:09:24,100 --> 00:09:26,980
But what about Mother?

162
00:09:35,140 --> 00:09:35,980
Shopkeeper Hao.

163
00:09:37,260 --> 00:09:38,100
Shopkeeper Hao.

164
00:09:39,460 --> 00:09:40,380
Young Master.

165
00:09:40,380 --> 00:09:42,540
Sell all the inventory at a 70% discount,

166
00:09:43,140 --> 00:09:45,660
and then buy some gold
and silver materials.

167
00:09:46,860 --> 00:09:48,780
Sell at a 70% discount?

168
00:09:49,020 --> 00:09:50,420
We have no other choice.

169
00:09:51,140 --> 00:09:53,220
Over a hundred people
in Qipei Pavilion need to eat.

170
00:09:53,220 --> 00:09:54,340
We have to take a chance.

171
00:09:54,620 --> 00:09:56,820
You decide. I'll handle it.

172
00:09:58,780 --> 00:09:59,660
Thank you.

173
00:10:07,140 --> 00:10:09,580
I thought Pei had some backbone.

174
00:10:10,220 --> 00:10:11,540
But he's selling out

175
00:10:11,540 --> 00:10:12,980
his family assets.

176
00:10:13,220 --> 00:10:14,900
That's called karma.

177
00:10:15,380 --> 00:10:18,220
Even if he sells the inventory at a loss,

178
00:10:18,220 --> 00:10:20,420
he can't last without supplies.

179
00:10:20,740 --> 00:10:25,340
So let's watch them run out of resources.

180
00:10:25,620 --> 00:10:27,900
Maybe I should help.

181
00:10:28,260 --> 00:10:31,300
Buy their remaining stock.

182
00:10:32,340 --> 00:10:35,140
And sell it at original prices.

183
00:10:35,380 --> 00:10:36,580
They'll be infuriated.

184
00:10:43,220 --> 00:10:44,100
Madam,

185
00:10:44,340 --> 00:10:46,820
I made this soup especially for you.

186
00:10:51,500 --> 00:10:52,340
Let me.

187
00:11:00,980 --> 00:11:02,020
It's just made.

188
00:11:13,500 --> 00:11:15,500
- Is it good?
- Tastes very good.

189
00:11:17,100 --> 00:11:17,980
Have some more.

190
00:11:18,380 --> 00:11:19,420
I'll do it myself.

191
00:11:20,220 --> 00:11:21,780
Alright, alright.

192
00:11:31,100 --> 00:11:34,460
The weather's nice today.

193
00:11:36,780 --> 00:11:38,460
Alright. Sit down.

194
00:11:46,340 --> 00:11:47,180
Dandan,

195
00:11:47,310 --> 00:11:48,540
you want to talk about Qipei Pavilion

196
00:11:48,540 --> 00:11:50,660
switching to gold
and silver jewelry, right?

197
00:11:54,140 --> 00:11:55,820
Are you angry?

198
00:11:59,780 --> 00:12:00,820
Honestly,

199
00:12:01,500 --> 00:12:03,220
I can't let go.

200
00:12:04,660 --> 00:12:06,100
Back then, Pei's father

201
00:12:06,900 --> 00:12:09,260
was in charge of the Crown,
but he lost it,

202
00:12:09,620 --> 00:12:12,340
causing Qipei Pavilion's reputation
to plummet.

203
00:12:14,500 --> 00:12:15,620
A few years later,

204
00:12:16,140 --> 00:12:17,940
he passed away unexpectedly.

205
00:12:19,460 --> 00:12:22,500
Qipei Pavilion was in debt,

206
00:12:22,860 --> 00:12:23,980
and we had

207
00:12:24,540 --> 00:12:25,540
to pawn our house

208
00:12:25,980 --> 00:12:27,220
and shop.

209
00:12:28,500 --> 00:12:29,860
After repaying the debt,

210
00:12:30,260 --> 00:12:33,260
we were left with nothing.

211
00:12:34,860 --> 00:12:36,620
Everyone in Yuncui City

212
00:12:37,500 --> 00:12:39,180
thought Pei and I

213
00:12:39,380 --> 00:12:40,820
would give up on Qipei Pavilion

214
00:12:41,140 --> 00:12:42,660
and find another way to live.

215
00:12:45,140 --> 00:12:48,420
But I stubbornly held on until now.

216
00:12:49,140 --> 00:12:50,540
Pack up your things and leave.

217
00:12:50,540 --> 00:12:52,020
Not a penny of the rent can be owed.

218
00:12:52,020 --> 00:12:52,980
Sir,

219
00:12:53,340 --> 00:12:55,060
just give me one more month.

220
00:12:55,460 --> 00:12:56,540
I can pay you daily

221
00:12:56,740 --> 00:12:58,340
from the sales.

222
00:12:58,620 --> 00:13:00,100
And after the business is done,

223
00:13:00,340 --> 00:13:01,660
the rent will be paid in full.

224
00:13:01,860 --> 00:13:03,980
You, a woman with a child,

225
00:13:03,980 --> 00:13:04,980
think you can do business?

226
00:13:04,980 --> 00:13:06,340
I don't believe you can sell anything.

227
00:13:06,340 --> 00:13:07,780
I can do it.

228
00:13:07,780 --> 00:13:08,900
Trust me.

229
00:13:08,900 --> 00:13:10,460
Please give me another chance.

230
00:13:10,460 --> 00:13:12,020
Why should I give you a chance?

231
00:13:12,260 --> 00:13:13,500
Pack up and leave,

232
00:13:13,500 --> 00:13:14,620
- or I'll smash everything.
- Sir.

233
00:13:14,620 --> 00:13:15,540
Please help us.

234
00:13:15,540 --> 00:13:17,380
Sir.

235
00:13:18,260 --> 00:13:19,100
Mother,

236
00:13:19,340 --> 00:13:21,380
why do we have to do the jade business?

237
00:13:22,140 --> 00:13:23,340
Why do you insist?

238
00:13:26,500 --> 00:13:27,340
Pei,

239
00:13:28,380 --> 00:13:29,500
remember this.

240
00:13:29,900 --> 00:13:31,420
One day, I will

241
00:13:31,900 --> 00:13:34,580
put the Qipei Pavilion sign back up.

242
00:13:42,020 --> 00:13:43,500
No one knows

243
00:13:44,500 --> 00:13:46,420
how much I've suffered,

244
00:13:46,860 --> 00:13:48,340
how many grievances I've endured.

245
00:13:49,860 --> 00:13:51,020
But no matter what,

246
00:13:51,020 --> 00:13:52,580
I held on.

247
00:13:54,740 --> 00:13:55,820
Madam,

248
00:13:56,380 --> 00:13:58,020
you have always been my role model.

249
00:13:58,540 --> 00:14:01,740
Whether in life or in skills,

250
00:14:02,020 --> 00:14:04,340
I've learned a lot from you.

251
00:14:07,140 --> 00:14:07,980
Dandan,

252
00:14:08,740 --> 00:14:10,780
from the moment I saw you,

253
00:14:11,260 --> 00:14:12,940
I chose you for Qipei Pavilion

254
00:14:13,380 --> 00:14:14,300
because

255
00:14:14,620 --> 00:14:15,740
I saw

256
00:14:16,020 --> 00:14:17,860
my younger self in you.

257
00:14:18,140 --> 00:14:20,060
That fearless spirit

258
00:14:20,380 --> 00:14:22,140
is just like mine.

259
00:14:23,460 --> 00:14:24,540
So,

260
00:14:25,380 --> 00:14:26,460
I believe in you.

261
00:14:27,900 --> 00:14:31,300
So you agree to Qipei Pavilion

262
00:14:31,710 --> 00:14:32,940
switching to gold and silver jewelry?

263
00:14:33,260 --> 00:14:34,380
I am old.

264
00:14:35,220 --> 00:14:37,140
I can't hold onto everything.

265
00:14:37,140 --> 00:14:40,180
It's time to let you all take a chance.

266
00:14:43,740 --> 00:14:46,140
Don't worry.
It's just a temporary measure.

267
00:14:46,140 --> 00:14:47,260
We will never give up

268
00:14:47,260 --> 00:14:49,180
the hundred-year reputation
of Qipei Pavilion's jade.

269
00:14:49,860 --> 00:14:51,700
We just need some time.

270
00:14:53,980 --> 00:14:54,860
I swear.

271
00:14:55,140 --> 00:14:57,620
Qipei Pavilion will shine again.

272
00:14:57,620 --> 00:14:59,700
I will not disappoint you.

273
00:15:00,380 --> 00:15:01,220
Okay.

274
00:15:01,220 --> 00:15:02,140
Really.

275
00:15:02,140 --> 00:15:03,060
I believe you.

276
00:15:03,660 --> 00:15:04,500
Good.

277
00:15:05,140 --> 00:15:06,140
Just trust me.

278
00:15:14,540 --> 00:15:17,980
(Delight and Peace)

279
00:15:49,780 --> 00:15:51,700
(Huaizhou)

280
00:15:51,700 --> 00:15:53,380
(Qipei Pavilion)

281
00:16:01,660 --> 00:16:02,580
It's done.

282
00:16:03,500 --> 00:16:04,420
Looks beautiful.

283
00:16:07,740 --> 00:16:10,700
Ms. Shuangshuang,
